    "shortDescription": "European pine martens are mustelids — relatives of weasels and otters — found across much of Europe and parts of western Asia. They have chocolate-brown fur, a creamy yellow throat patch, sharp senses, and claws that help them climb through branches. Fun fact: Pine martens are mostly active at dusk and night, slipping through trees after small animals, insects, eggs, berries, and nuts."
